Package org.certificateservices.custom.c2x.ieee1609dot2.datastructs.secureddata

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Countersignature
    This data structure is used to perform a countersignature over an already-signed SPDU.
    HashedData
    This structure contains the hash of some data with a specified hash algorithm.
    HeaderInfo
    This structure contains information that is used to establish validity by the criteria of 5.2.
    Ieee1609Dot2Content
    In this structure:
    Ieee1609Dot2Data
    This data type is used to contain the other data types in this clause.
    MissingCrlIdentifier
    This structure may be used to request a CRL that the SSME knows to have been issued but has not yet received.
    SignedData
    In this structure: hashId indicates the hash algorithm to be used to generate the hash of the message for signing and verification.
    SignedDataPayload
    This structure contains the data payload of a ToBeSignedData.
    SignerIdentifier
    This structure allows the recipient of data to determine which keying material to use to authenticate the data.
    ToBeSignedData
    This structure contains the data to be hashed when generating or verifying a signature.
